the night before joel steinbergs adoptive 
6yearold daughter was removed unconscious from their apartment 
his livein companion said she heard noises in a bedroom like joel 
throwing lisa sources said monday 
hedda nussbaum told a psychiatrist at columbia presbyterian 
medical center on nov 20 that steinberg who is accused of beating 
lisa steinberg to death then handed the child to her saying 
this is your child what have you done this has gone far 
enough wcbstv said monday quoting from a copy of the 
unidentified psychiatrists report 
the associated press confirmed the contents of the report through 
sources close to the case 
nussbaum told the psychiatrist that steinberg was angry that 
night because lisa refused to drink water after he had given her and 
nussbaum hot pepper she said he gave them the hot pepper to get 
them to drink more water 
she later heard noises from the bedroom that sounded like joel 
throwing lisa the report said 
afterward steinberg gave the child to nussbaum who placed her 
on the floor and noticed water and food coming out of her mouth 
the report said that nussbaum thought joel may have poured water 
down lisas mouth and that she was drowning nussbaum said she then 
began pumping the childs chest 
nussbaum told the psychiatrist that steinberg had left the 
apartment shortly afterward and returned about 10 pm at about 6 
am steinberg said shes stopped breathing and told nussbaum 
to call 911 
nussbaum 46 a former editor of childrens books also was 
charged with lisas murder but the charges against her later were 
dropped 
she has spent the last year undergoing physical and psychiatric 
rehabilitation for injuries the prosecution says she suffered at 
steinbergs hands 
at steinbergs trial on monday a photographer testified that he 
used poses and lighting tricks to hide bruises he saw on the 
battered child when he took pictures of her in school two weeks 
before she was found dead 
stuart gross working that day for scholastic books said he 
initially was reluctant to photograph the firstgrader when he 
visited her school on oct 22 1987 because of her numerous bruises 
and her unkempt appearance 
i observed some bruises underneath her left eye by the cheeks 
a bump on the forehead and underneath the chin here a bruise and 
some bruises on her arms gross said the hair was very unkempt 
uneven and her clothes were very rumpled dirty he said 
gross said he eventually took several black and white pictures of 
lisa he said he was drawn to her when she began directing two other 
children on posing the way he wanted them she seemed older more 
mature he said 
i put her on the right side and i flooded my light into her and 
i had her turn her head this way and down so you wouldnt see it 
the last thing my client wants to see is bruises gross said 
he said the rumpled and dirty quality of lisas clothing also was 
eliminated in the way i photographed them 
steinberg 47 is charged with murder for allegedly beating lisa 
to death the disbarred lawyer denies that he hit the child he says 
she fell unconscious after choking on food she had vomited 
lisa was taken unconscious from steinbergs greenwich village 
apartment early on nov 2 1987 and died three days later at a 
hospital 
prosecutors are trying to show by gross photographs and 
testimony that lisa was an abused child in the weeks before her 
death they hope to eliminate any reasonable inference except that 
the abuse was inflicted by steinberg who illegally adopted the girl 
