<TEXT>
north korean clams have been imported 
to south korea the first product to arrive since the seoul 
government approved a policy allowing direct trade with north korea 
a customs spokesman said today that 40 pounds of shortnecked 
clams from north korea had cleared customs at the port city of 
pusan half the shipment was frozen and half were dried the 
spokesman said 
the clams were brought to south korea by way of japan by hyundai 
corp a general trading company as food samples in preparation for 
expansion of trading with the north 
the seoul government approved the resumption of direct trade of 
all but military goods in october as a gesture of goodwill in 
efforts to ease tension and improve relations between the two koreas 
goods from the communist north had been banned since the division 
of the peninsula after world war ii 
