us customs service inspectors seized more 
than 1400 pounds of highgrade cocaine with an estimated street 
value of 28 million the customs service said monday 
the cocaine was found nov 11 in suburban jefferson in a shipment 
of 55gallon drums of resin from guatemala but announcement of the 
confiscation was delayed because customs wanted to try to catch the 
buyers said spokeswoman liz orgeron 
what we were trying to do was make a controlled delivery to see 
if we could make an arrest said orgeron 
