the 1424 pounds of the drug was turned over to the drug enforcement 
administration 
the seizure was the largest ever in new orleans said orgeron 
she said the cocaine was on a ship that carried goods from 
central america a fact that prompted customs agents to look 
closely at the cargo the resin containers got special attention 
because resin rarely comes into the port of new orleans she said 
she said the customs contraband enforcement team drilled into 60 
