<TEXT>
the illinois supreme court set the stage 
monday for chicagos third mayoral freeforall in six years ruling 
that voters must decide who serves the last two years of the late 
mayor harold washingtons term 
siding with city officials who scheduled a feb 28 primary and an 
april 4 general election next year rather than waiting until 1991 
the court said mayor eugene sawyers appointment by the city council 
after washingtons death does not extend through 1991 when 
washingtons term ends 
washington died of a heart attack on nov 25 1987 less than 
eight months after winning a second term 
the seven justices ruled without written dissent that state laws 
governing vacancies in office were designed to ensure that an 
appointed official would not serve such a long portion of an 
unexpired term 
supporters of a 1991 election had argued their case was supported 
by the state election code which says the mayor of chicago should 
be chosen in a spring election every four years beginning in 1979 
the court said that only prescribes regularly scheduled elections 
where the incumbent official continues in office 
sawyer who supported a 1991 election but has indicated he is 
prepared to run next year said he was pleased that this decision 
has been made and that the people in chicago are no longer in 
limbo 
we are ready for the upcoming election and look forward to 
winning it said sawyer who raised nearly 3 million in less than 
a year against the possibility of a spring election 
the ruling also drew applause from the field of announced and 
wouldbe candidates poised to make next years mayoral race the most 
crowded in the citys recent history 
i think its the decision the public wanted said alderman 
lawrence bloom a staunch washington ally who was among the first to 
announce his candidacy for a 1989 mayoral race they didnt want 
29 members of the city council to elect their mayor for three 
years 
cook county states attorney richard m daley widely reported to 
be planning a second bid for the job his father held for two 
decades said he would make an announcement in the next two 
weeks 
this is a serious decision daley said 
