candidates davis alderman edward burke former chicago parks 
district superintendent edmund kelly and undecided 
the possibility of three black candidates sawyer evans and 
davis raises the possibility of a split in the black voting bloc 
that made washington the citys first black mayor in 1983 and 
lifted him to reelection in 1987 
such a split would strengthen daley who split the white vote 
