asir sandler remembers the 
interrogation the death sentence never carried out and the tiny 
knots he tied in pieces of string to remind him of what he saw in a 
stalinist labor camp north of this capital of the gulag 
trudy richter a german communist whose nationality couldnt save 
her remembers the filthy crowded ferry ride from vladivostok to 
magadan and her husband who never returned 
this city of the soviet far east like so much of the soviet 
union is torn between the urge to remember and the desire to forget 
josef stalins purges that put it on the map and gave it the fearful 
reputation it still is trying to outlive 
thousands of stalins political prisoners were sent through 
magadan nothing more than a couple of stone buildings and wooden 
barracks in the 1930s on their way north to the gold mines and 
labor camps of the kolyma region of the far northeast 
sandler 71 a native of baku in the warm southern republic of 
azerbaijan spent the last several of his 10 years of labor camp as 
prisoner m1866 in a camp in the kolyma region 
he met with foreign reporters in magadan recently to show them 
how he made the coded knots in pieces of string to record what he 
saw those strings hidden in the camp and smuggled out by a means 
he still wont reveal gave him some of the materials he has used to 
write about camp life 
your life there was hanging by a hair every minute he said 
you could be strangled by criminals for your portion of water and 
your piece of bread 
halfstarved prisoners nevertheless were required to be neat and 
even a loose corner on his number badge could mean 10 days in a 
punishment cell on only 200 grams of bread and a cup of boiled water 
a day 
sandler arrived in the magadan region in 1947 already a prisoner 
for many years after being accused of spying for germany during 
world war ii during a long interrogation the charge eventually was 
reduced to carrying a poem in his pocket that insulted stalin 
a military tribunal in baku sentenced him to be shot but allowed 
him to ask for clemency and then let him sit for another 90 days 
while the stress built up and his weight dropped from 70 kilograms 
154 pounds to 42 kilograms 92 pounds 
in the end he realized it was better to be a spy than to 
threaten stalin sandler said i understood that if i didnt 
sign what the investigator wanted i wouldnt live another two 
months 
stories such as sandlers have given magadan a reputation 
difficult to outlive 
magadan is regarded as a city of sad fate this we remember and 
