<TEXT>
with more than 25000 restaurants within its 
borders new york city might well be considered the culinary 
crossroads of the world 
diners can choose from what the new york convention and visitors 
bureau describes as a cornucopia of international cuisines 
including brazilian cajun chinese french german greek indian 
italian japanese mexican russian spanish thai or vietnamese 
specialties 
but at rockefeller center in the very heart of manhattan 
patrons also might encounter such attractions as breakfast at the 
ok corral lunch selections from the firefighters cookbook 
or a dinner menu built around recipes borrowed from the tasty meals 
served to ringling brothers and barnum amp bailey circus performers 
such offbeat items are most often seen on the menus of the 
american festival cafe one of three restaurants wrapped around the 
famed iceskating rink which becomes an open air garden cafe during 
the warm weather season 
the other two eateries are the elegant sea grill which 
specializes in seafood and savories a casual restaurant geared to 
speedy service and takeout delectables the emphasis at all three is 
on allamerican dining the wine list is strictly domestic and the 
beer choices feature regional american brews 
customers at the american festival when the ok corral 
breakfast was offered in 1986 found such imaginative menu offerings 
as apples baked in bourbon eggs scrambled with frizzled beef jerky 
oatmeal flapjacks with molassesstewed prunes and judge roy beans 
beans 
ruth epstein who has helped plan and promote such 
offthebeatentrack themes since the restaurant opened four years 
ago explains how beans usually were prepared in the judges wild 
west days 
by the time the pale pink beans called arizona strawberries had 
cooked all night in their covering of bourbon onions molasses 
salt pork and spices the bourbons alcohol had entirely evaporated 
leaving behind only the mellow smoky flavor of kentuckys pride as a 
reminder of the previous evenings carouse 
according to miss epstein public relations consultant for 
restaurant associates which operates the three eateries adopting 
new themes and changing menus several times a year is not a simple 
task especially when the restaurant serves about 450000 meals 
annually matching the combined total of 450000 meals served at the 
other two restaurants 
its not the easiest thing in the world to do with a 
restaurant because change as it is for people is difficult for 
restaurants you have to extend yourself to change rather than keep 
on doing the same thing she explains 
changing a menu requires an extraordinary pulling together of a 
very large team everybody has to cooperate when you have a 
changewhen i have an idea sometimes even supplying recipes for 
them the chef is always there because the cooking people are 
involved from the beginning 
theres also the purchasing and marketing departments and the 
liquor buyers and so on then when the new menu is set and tested 
and ready to be printed on paper it involves everybody in the 
restaurant who serves it 
there are meetings by our management staff to teach people who 
serve it what it is how it looks how it tastes how its served 
when firehouse cooking was the theme early last year the 
program was billed as a tribute to americas firehouse chefs all of 
the recipes were created by firefighters and most were taken from 
john sinenos bestselling the firefighters cookbook 
during the testing of the chefs cooking of recipes being 
considered for the menu the firefighters tasting panel discovered 
something new miss epstein recalls 
as she explained in the american festival newsletter 
they pointed out that there must be some mistake in the 
manicotti delicious as it was and please pass some more theirs 
had never had a sauce like that it took our forensic team some time 
to determine that two recipes had inadvertently been combined and 
that danny princes manicotti had been topped with a sauce based on 
his artichoke pie thus are great dishes born 
it was named manicotti with accidental sauce and was the 
first dish to earn a place on the firehouse cooking menu 
the circus theme featured a menu recalling the days when ringling 
brothers and company played under canvas and traveled on a train a 
hundred cars long carrying some 1400 people lions tigers and 
elephants 
the fun menu the cooking of the circus stars was printed in 
red white and blue and borrowed the traditional hyperbole of circus 
promotions it declared the offerings as the most gorgeous and 
princely spectacle of monumental magnificence ever beforked 
 
