<TEXT>
a federal judge will hear motions next month 
stemming from three jurors claims that they were intimidated into 
voting for an 815 million judgment against the maker of the copper 
7 intrauterine device monsanto co said monday 
monsanto whose gd searle amp co subsidiary manufactured the 
copper 7 on monday released a letter that the jurors sent to us 
district judge robert renner who presided over the trial 
the jury on sept 9 awarded the damages to esther kociemba who 
claimed the birth control device had left her infertile 
the three jurors whose names were withheld at their request 
also indicated they did not believe the plaintiff proved her claim 
that the device caused her injuries 
the judgment represented the first jury award of punitive damages 
against searle in a copper 7 case the pharmaceutical company has 
won 15 of 19 copper 7 damage cases that have gone before a jury 
monsanto spokesman mark l schannon said searle attorneys would 
introduce motions to vacate the award 
renner will hear the motions dec 1 in us district court at st 
paul minn schannon said renner can let the verdict stand reduce 
the award or order a new trial schannon said 
the letter from the three jurors claimed that continual verbal 
harassment and intimidation by the jury foreman during 
deliberations prevented them from expressing their opinion about the 
trial evidence 
our failure to understand the purpose andor power of the jury 
foreman facilitated our inability to express individual opinions 
the letter read 
the three jurors also stated that a desire to inform the court of 
a 44 split among jury was prevented by a convenient 
interpretation of the jury and judges instructions 
any opinions which conflicted with the foremans plaintiffs 
views were met with disdain and contempt and resulted in additional 
verbal andor physical harassment the letter said when the 
obvious difference of opinion became apparent discussions and 
negotiations ceased 
while believing that searle may have been negligent in 
advertising we individually assessed that esther kociemba never 
proved that the cu7 caused her injuries the letter read 
summarily we individually and collectively feel ashamed and 
embarrassed to be associated with a verdict against our true 
opinions the three wrote 
richard s duesenberg monsantos general counsel said the 
jurors wrote the letter on their own initiative and neither monsanto 
nor searle saw the letter until it was received by renner 
this is an important letter for our shareholders for two 
reasons first the plaintiffs attorneys failed to convince the 
full jury that the cu7 cause the plaintiffs injuries and second 
this case should not be viewed as a watershed duesenberg said 
in minnesota mrs kociembas attorney issued a statement 
labeling the letter legally irrelevant and accusing searle lawyers 
of having met with the three jurors 
this is simploy a desperate and futile attempt by searle and 
monsanto to achieve a result they couldnt achieve in court 
stated lawyer michael ciresi this is nothing more than 
postverdict jury tampering 
